    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nLSP diagnostics get stuck / stop working after running :e! command on neovim. See screenrecording:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/36432023/f9cadf18-83a1-4c8c-9518-9dec2d1b327a\r\n\r\n_Note: originally reported here_ https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/2909\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\ninit.vim\r\n```\r\ncall plug#begin('~/.vim-plugged')\r\nPlug 'neovim/nvim-lspconfig'\r\ncall plug#end()\r\n\r\nlua <<EOF\r\n  local lspconfig = require('lspconfig')\r\n  require('lspconfig')['tsserver'].setup {}\r\nEOF\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. Setup a language server, like shown above\r\n2. Make a file change that triggers a diagnostic\r\n3. Write :e! on neovim command mode and press Enter\r\n4. Now the diagnostic is stuck, it won't work for that particular file until you restart :LspRestart\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDiagnostics shouldn't be stuck, they should be able to keep working after :e! and be updated based on the latest changes to the buffer.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.4\n\n### Language server name/version\n\ntypescript-language-server@4.1.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian GNU/Linux VERSION=\"10 (buster)\"\n\n### Log file\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/andrescuco/930182635d7acdbbb174eae6a2e5a1e4",
